1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
It was rather interesting just to watch them gathering their materials and bouncing around

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,500
their, what do they call it, kangaroo walk or something like that.

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,500
Who named it that?

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,500
I don't know.

5
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:19,000
I bet those men are going to get quite a reception when they get back to New York.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Oh yes, I'll be so glad when they land back now.

7
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:30,000
I think that's pretty well a fact because they've landed so many safely now.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
and I feel relief. Just getting off of the moon was the thing that was...

9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Have they met with the one that was circling?

10
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Yes, they've rendezvoused. So I understand. That wasn't shown either, so I...

11
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
But they say they have rendezvoused, so...

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:53,000
That's a matter of making the circles and then coming down.

13
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,000
What do you sort of imagine for the future? Do you imagine them sending a...

14
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
I think they will. I think they will.

15
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
And we'll do some more exploring up there.

16
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Very positive.

17
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Because that was such a very small area, when you think of it, that they just gathered rocks and, oh, samples of soil and all.

18
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:22,000
And they did a probe for some samples.

19
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
And just what was going to come of that, I don't know. I'd be glad to read it.

